A degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field;
Experienced writing production quality code in Python, including dependency management (Poetry or uv) and testing frameworks (pytest);
Experienced with the engineering concepts of some of popular Machine Learning libraries (TensorFlow, PyTorch), platforms (MLflow, Weights and Biases) and orchestrators (Airflow, Metaflow);
Experienced with CI/CD systems (i.e. Azure Pipelines, ArgoCD);
Proficient in building and maintaining APIs (FastAPI, Flask) and familiar with documentation tools (Swagger/OpenAPI);
Familiar with containerization tools like docker;
Knowledge of core AI/ML techniques;
Experience working with modern monitoring system observability (Prometheus, Grafana, Open Telemetry);
Hands-on experience in developing infrastructure as code with Terraform;
Experience in working with JIRA and Confluence in an Agile environment;
Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work in a team environment;
Thoughtful, thorough and conscientious;
Critical thinking and ability to show initiative;
Open and receptive to new and different ideas;




